-- # Class: NetworkTraffic Description: The Network Traffic object describes characteristics of network traffic over atime period. The metrics represent network data transferred between source anddestination during an observation window.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: bytes Description: The total number of bytes transferred in both directions (sum of bytes_in andbytes_out).
--     * Slot: bytes_in Description: The number of bytes sent from the destination to the source (inbounddirection).
--     * Slot: bytes_missed Description: The number of bytes that were missed during observation, typically due topacket loss or sampling limitations.
--     * Slot: bytes_out Description: The number of bytes sent from the source to the destination (outbounddirection).
--     * Slot: chunks Description: The total number of chunks transferred in both directions (sum of chunks_in andchunks_out).
--     * Slot: chunks_in Description: The number of chunks sent from the destination to the source (inbounddirection).
--     * Slot: chunks_out Description: The number of chunks sent from the source to the destination (outbounddirection).
--     * Slot: end_time Description: The end time of the observation or reporting period.
--     * Slot: packets Description: The total number of packets transferred in both directions (sum of packets_inand packets_out).
--     * Slot: packets_in Description: The number of packets sent from the destination to the source (inbounddirection).
--     * Slot: packets_out Description: The number of packets sent from the source to the destination (outbounddirection).
--     * Slot: start_time Description: The start time of the observation or reporting period.
--     * Slot: timespan_id Description: The time span object representing the duration of the observation or reportingperiod.
-- # Class: Node Description: Represents a node or a vertex in a graph structure.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: data Description: Additional data about the node stored as key-value pairs. Can include customproperties specific to the node.
--     * Slot: desc Description: A human-readable description of the node's purpose or meaning in the graph.
--     * Slot: name Description: A human-readable name or label for the node. Should be descriptive and uniquewithin the graph context.
--     * Slot: type Description: Categorizes the node into a specific class or type. Useful for grouping andfiltering nodes.
--     * Slot: uid Description: A unique string or numeric identifier that distinguishes this node from allothers in the graph. Must be unique across all nodes.
-- # Class: Organization Description: The Organization object describes characteristics of an organization or companyand its division if any. Additionally, it also describes cloud andSoftware-as-a-Service (SaaS) logical hierarchies such as AWS Organizations,Google Cloud Organizations, Oracle Cloud Tenancies, and similar constructs.
