--     * Slot: type Description: The policy type. For example: <code>Identity Policy, Resource Policy, ServiceControl Policy, etc.</code>.
--     * Slot: uid Description: A unique identifier of the policy instance.
--     * Slot: version Description: The policy version number.
--     * Slot: group_id Description: The policy group.
-- # Class: ProcessEntity Description: The Process Entity object provides critical fields for referencing a process.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: cmd_line Description: The full command line used to launch an application, service, process, or job.For example: <code>ssh user@10.0.0.10</code>. If the command line isunavailable or missing, the empty string <code>''</code> is to be used.
--     * Slot: cpid Description: A unique process identifier that can be assigned deterministically by multiplesystem data producers.
--     * Slot: created_time Description: The time when the process was created/started.
--     * Slot: name Description: The friendly name of the process, for example: <code>Notepad++</code>.
--     * Slot: path Description: The process file path.
--     * Slot: pid Description: The process identifier, as reported by the operating system. Process ID (PID)is a number used by the operating system to uniquely identify an activeprocess.
--     * Slot: uid Description: A unique identifier for this process assigned by the producer (tool).Facilitates correlation of a process event with other events for that process.
-- # Class: Product Description: The Product object describes characteristics of a software product.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: cpe_name Description: The Common Platform Enumeration (CPE) name as described by (<a target='_blank'href='https://nvd.nist.gov/products/cpe'>NIST</a>) For example:<code>cpe:/a:apple:safari:16.2</code>.
--     * Slot: lang Description: The two letter lower case language codes, as defined by <a target='_blank'href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_639-1'>ISO 639-1</a>. For example:<code>en</code> (English), <code>de</code> (German), or <code>fr</code>(French).
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the product.
--     * Slot: path Description: The installation path of the product.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The unique identifier of the product.
--     * Slot: url_string Description: The URL pointing towards the product.
--     * Slot: vendor_name Description: The name of the vendor of the product.
--     * Slot: version Description: The version of the product, as defined by the event source. For example:<code>2013.1.3-beta</code>.
--     * Slot: feature_id Description: The feature that reported the event.
--     * Slot: data_classification_id Description: The Data Classification object includes information about data classificationlevels and data category types.
-- # Class: QueryInfo Description: The query info object holds information related to data access within adatastore. To access, manipulate, delete, or retrieve data from a datastore, aquery must be written using a specific syntax.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: bytes Description: The size of the data returned from the query.
--     * Slot: data Description: The data returned from the query execution.
--     * Slot: name Description: The query name for a saved or scheduled query.
--     * Slot: query_string Description: A string representing the query code being run. For example: <code>SELECT *FROM my_table</code>
--     * Slot: query_time Description: The time when the query was run.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The unique identifier of the query.
-- # Class: Reporter Description: The entity from which an event or finding was reported.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: hostname Description: The hostname of the entity from which the event or finding was reported.
--     * Slot: ip Description: The IP address of the entity from which the event or finding was reported.
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the entity from which the event or finding was reported.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The unique identifier of the entity from which the event or finding wasreported.
--     * Slot: org_id Description: The organization properties of the entity that reported the event or finding.
-- # Class: ResourceDetails Description: The Resource Details object describes details about resources that wereaffected by the activity/event.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: cloud_partition Description: The logical grouping or isolated segment within a cloud provider'sinfrastructure where the resource is located. Examples include AWS partitions(aws, aws-cn, aws-us-gov), Azure cloud environments (AzureCloud,AzureUSGovernment, AzureChinaCloud), or similar logical divisions in othercloud providers.
--     * Slot: criticality Description: The criticality of the resource as defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: hostname Description: The fully qualified name of the resource.
--     * Slot: ip Description: The IP address of the resource, in either IPv4 or IPv6 format.
--     * Slot: is_backed_up Description: Indicates whether the device or resource has a backup enabled, such as anautomated snapshot or a cloud backup. For example, this is indicated by the<code>cloudBackupEnabled</code> value within JAMF Pro mobile devices or theregistration of an AWS ARN with the AWS Backup service.
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the resource.
--     * Slot: namespace Description: The namespace is useful when similar entities exist that you need to keepseparate.
--     * Slot: provider Description: The cloud service provider that hosts or manages the resource. This field istypically used when the resource is managed by a different provider than theone generating the event or finding. Examples include AWS, Azure, GCP (GoogleCloud Platform), Oracle Cloud, IBM Cloud, Alibaba Cloud, or other public,private, or hybrid cloud providers.
--     * Slot: region Description: The cloud region where the resource is hosted, as defined by the cloudprovider. This represents the physical or logical geographic area containingthe infrastructure supporting the resource. Examples include AWS regions(us-east-1, eu-west-1), Azure regions (East US, West Europe), GCP regions(us-central1, europe-west1), or Oracle Cloud regions (us-ashburn-1,uk-london-1).
--     * Slot: role Description: The role of the resource in the context of the event or finding, normalized tothe caption of the role_id value. In the case of 'Other', it is defined by theevent source.
--     * Slot: role_id Description: The normalized identifier of the resource's role in the context of the event orfinding.
--     * Slot: version Description: The version of the resource. For example <code>1.2.3</code>.
--     * Slot: zone Description: The availability zone within a cloud region where the resource is located.Examples include AWS availability zones (us-east-1a, us-east-1b), Azureavailability zones (1, 2, 3 within a region), GCP zones (us-central1-a,us-central1-b), or Oracle Cloud availability domains (AD-1, AD-2, AD-3).
--     * Slot: created_time Description: The time when the resource was created.
--     * Slot: data Description: Additional data describing the resource.
--     * Slot: modified_time Description: The time when the resource was last modified.
--     * Slot: type Description: The resource type as defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The unique identifier of the resource.
--     * Slot: uid_alt Description: The alternative unique identifier of the resource.
--     * Slot: group_id Description: The name of the related resource group.
--     * Slot: owner_id Description: The details of the entity that owns the resource. This object includesproperties such as the owner's name, unique identifier, type, domain, and otherrelevant attributes that help identify the resource owner within theenvironment.
--     * Slot: resource_relationship_id Description: A graph representation showing how this resource relates to and interacts withother entities in the environment. This can include parent/child relationships,dependencies, or other connections.
--     * Slot: api_id Description: Describes details about a typical API (Application Programming Interface) call.
--     * Slot: cloud_id Description: Describes details about the Cloud environment where the event or finding wascreated.
--     * Slot: data_classification_id Description: The Data Classification object includes information about data classificationlevels and data category types.
-- # Class: Rule Description: The Rule object describes characteristics of a rule associated with a policy oran event.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: category Description: The rule category.
--     * Slot: desc Description: The description of the rule that generated the event.
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the rule that generated the event.
--     * Slot: type Description: The rule type.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The unique identifier of the rule that generated the event.
--     * Slot: version Description: The rule version. For example: <code>1.1</code>.
-- # Class: Scan Description: The Scan object describes characteristics of a proactive scan.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: name Description: The administrator-supplied or application-generated name of the scan. Forexample: "Home office weekly user database scan", "Scan folders for viruses","Full system virus scan"
--     * Slot: type Description: The type of scan.
--     * Slot: type_id Description: The type id of the scan.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The application-defined unique identifier assigned to an instance of a scan.
-- # Class: Service Description: The Service object describes characteristics of a service, <code> e.g. AWS EC2.</code>
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the service.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The unique identifier of the service.
--     * Slot: version Description: The version of the service.
-- # Class: SubTechnique Description: The MITRE Sub-technique object describes the ATT&CK® or ATLAS™ Sub-technique IDand/or name associated to an attack.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the attack sub-technique. For example: <code>Scanning IPBlocks</code> or <code>User Execution: Unsafe ML Artifacts</code>.
--     * Slot: src_url Description: The versioned permalink of the attack sub-technique. For example:<code>https://attack.mitre.org/versions/v14/techniques/T1595/001/</code>.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The unique identifier of the attack sub-technique. For example:<code>T1595.001</code> or <code>AML.T0011.000</code>.
-- # Class: Table Description: The table object represents a table within a structured relational database ordatastore, which contains columns and rows of data that are able to be create,updated, deleted and queried.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: created_time Description: The time when the table was known to have been created.
--     * Slot: desc Description: The description of the table.
--     * Slot: modified_time Description: The most recent time when any changes, updates, or modifications were madewithin the table.
--     * Slot: name Description: The table name, ordinarily as assigned by a database administrator.
--     * Slot: size Description: The size of the data table in bytes.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The unique identifier of the table.
-- # Class: Tactic Description: The MITRE Tactic object describes the ATT&CK® or ATLAS™ Tactic ID and/or namethat is associated to an attack.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: name Description: The Tactic name that is associated with the attack technique. For example:<code>Reconnaissance</code> or <code>ML Model Access</code>.
--     * Slot: src_url Description: The versioned permalink of the Tactic. For example:<code>https://attack.mitre.org/versions/v14/tactics/TA0043/</code>.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The Tactic ID that is associated with the attack technique. For example:<code>TA0043</code>, or <code>AML.TA0000</code>.
-- # Class: Technique Description: The MITRE Technique object describes the ATT&CK® or ATLAS™ Technique ID and/orname associated to an attack.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the attack technique. For example: <code>Active Scanning</code> or<code>AI Model Inference API Access</code>.
--     * Slot: src_url Description: The versioned permalink of the attack technique. For example:<code>https://attack.mitre.org/versions/v14/techniques/T1595/</code>.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The unique identifier of the attack technique. For example: <code>T1595</code>or <code>AML.T0040</code>.
-- # Class: Trait Description: Describes a characteristic or feature of an entity that was observed. Forexample, this object can be used to represent specific characteristics derivedfrom events or findings that can be surfaced as distinguishing traits of theentity in question.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: category Description: The high-level grouping or classification this trait belongs to.
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the trait.
--     * Slot: type Description: The type of the trait. For example, this can be used to indicate if the traitacts as a contributing factor (increases risk/severity) or a mitigating factor(decreases risk/severity), in the context of the related finding.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The unique identifier of the trait.
-- # Class: TransformationInfo Description: The transformation_info object represents the mapping or transformation used.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: lang Description: The transformation language used to transform the data.
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the transformation or mapping.
--     * Slot: time Description: Time of the transformation.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The unique identifier of the mapping or transformation.
--     * Slot: url_string Description: The Uniform Resource Locator String where the mapping or transformation exists.
--     * Slot: product_id Description: The product or instance used to make the transformation
-- # Class: UnmannedAerialSystem Description: The Unmanned Aerial System object describes the characteristics, PositionLocation Information (PLI), and other metadata of Unmanned Aerial Systems (UAS)and other unmanned and drone systems used in Remote ID. Remote ID is defined inthe Standard Specification for Remote ID and Tracking (ASTM Designation:F3411-22a) <a target='_blank'href='https://cdn.standards.iteh.ai/samples/112830/71297057ac42432880a203654f213709/ASTM-F3411-22a.pdf'>ASTMF3411-22a</a>.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the unmanned system as reported by tracking or sensing hardware.
--     * Slot: serial_number Description: The serial number of the unmanned system. This is expressed in<code>CTA-2063-A</code> format.
--     * Slot: type Description: The type of the UAS. For example, Helicopter, Gyroplane, Rocket, etc.
--     * Slot: type_id Description: The UAS type identifier.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The primary identification identifier for an unmanned system. This can be aSerial Number (in <code>CTA-2063-A</code> format, the Registration ID (providedby the <code>CAA</code>, a UTM, or a unique Session ID.
--     * Slot: uid_alt Description: A secondary identification identifier for an unmanned system. This can be aSerial Number (in <code>CTA-2063-A</code> format, the Registration ID (providedby the <code>CAA</code>, a UTM, or a unique Session ID.
--     * Slot: uuid Description: The Unmanned Aircraft System Traffic Management (UTM) provided universal uniqueID (UUID) traceable to a non-obfuscated ID where this UTM UUID acts as a'session id' to protect exposure of operationally sensitive information.
--     * Slot: model Description: The model name of the aircraft or unmanned system.
--     * Slot: speed Description: Ground speed of flight. This value is provided in meters per second with aminimum resolution of 0.25 m/s. Special Values: <code>Invalid</code>, <code>NoValue</code>, or <code>Unknown: 255 m/s</code>.
--     * Slot: speed_accuracy Description: Provides quality/containment on horizontal ground speed. Measured inmeters/second.
--     * Slot: track_direction Description: Direction of flight expressed as a “True North-based” ground track angle. Thisvalue is provided in clockwise degrees with a minimum resolution of 1 degree.If aircraft is not moving horizontally, use the “Unknown” value
--     * Slot: vertical_speed Description: Vertical speed upward relative to the WGS-84 datum, measured in meters persecond. Special Values: <code>Invalid</code>, <code>No Value</code>, or<code>Unknown: 63 m/s</code>.
--     * Slot: hw_info_id Description: The endpoint hardware information.
--     * Slot: location_id Description: The detailed geographical location usually associated with an IP address.
-- # Class: UnmannedSystemOperatingArea Description: The Unmanned System Operating Area object describes details about a precisearea of operations for a UAS flight or mission.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: altitude_ceiling Description: Maximum altitude (WGS-84 HAE) for a group or an Intent-Based NetworkParticipant. Measured in meters. Special Values: <code>Invalid</code>, <code>NoValue</code>, or <code>Unknown: -1000 m</code>.
--     * Slot: altitude_floor Description: Minimum altitude (WGS-84 HAE) for a group or an Intent-Based NetworkParticipant. Measured in meters. Special Values: <code>Invalid</code>, <code>NoValue</code>, or <code>Unknown: -1000 m</code>.
--     * Slot: count Description: Indicates the number of UAS in the operating area.
--     * Slot: end_time Description: The date and time at which a group or an Intent-Based Network Participantoperation ends. (This field is only applicable to Network Remote ID.)
--     * Slot: radius Description: Farthest horizontal distance from the reported location at which any UA in agroup may be located (meters). Also allows defining the area where anIntent-Based Network Participant operation is taking place. Default: 0 m.
--     * Slot: start_time Description: The date and time at which a group or an Intent-Based Network Participantoperation starts. (This field is only applicable to Network Remote ID.)
--     * Slot: type Description: The type of operating area. For example, <code>Takeoff Location</code>,<code>Fixed Location</code>, <code>Dynamic Location</code>.
--     * Slot: type_id Description: The operating area type identifier.
--     * Slot: aerial_height Description: Expressed as either height above takeoff location or height above ground level(AGL) for a UAS current location. This value is provided in meters and musthave a minimum resolution of 1 m. Special Values: <code>Invalid</code>,<code>No Value</code>, or <code>Unknown: -1000 m</code>.
--     * Slot: city Description: The name of the city.
--     * Slot: continent Description: The name of the continent.
--     * Slot: country Description: The ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 country code.<p><b>Note:</b> The two letter country codeshould be capitalized. For example: <code>US</code> or <code>CA</code>.</p>
--     * Slot: desc Description: The description of the geographical location.
--     * Slot: geodetic_altitude Description: The aircraft distance above or below the ellipsoid as measured along a linethat passes through the aircraft and is normal to the surface of the WGS-84ellipsoid. This value is provided in meters and must have a minimum resolutionof 1 m. Special Values: <code>Invalid</code>, <code>No Value</code>, or<code>Unknown: -1000 m</code>.
--     * Slot: geodetic_vertical_accuracy Description: Provides quality/containment on geodetic altitude. This is based on ADS-BGeodetic Vertical Accuracy (GVA). Measured in meters.
--     * Slot: geohash Description: <p>Geohash of the geo-coordinates (latitude and longitude).</p><atarget='_blank' href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geohash'>Geohashing</a> isa geocoding system used to encode geographic coordinates in decimal degrees, toa single string.
--     * Slot: horizontal_accuracy Description: Provides quality/containment on horizontal position. This is based on ADS-BNACp. Measured in meters.
--     * Slot: is_on_premises Description: Indicates whether the location is on-premises.
--     * Slot: isp Description: The name of the Internet Service Provider (ISP).
--     * Slot: lat Description: The geographical Latitude coordinate represented in Decimal Degrees (DD). Forexample: <code>42.361145</code>.
--     * Slot: long Description: The geographical Longitude coordinate represented in Decimal Degrees (DD). Forexample: <code>-71.057083</code>.
--     * Slot: postal_code Description: The postal code of the location.
--     * Slot: pressure_altitude Description: The uncorrected barometric pressure altitude (based on reference standard 29.92inHg, 1013.25 mb) provides a reference for algorithms that utilize 'altitudedeltas' between aircraft. This value is provided in meters and must have aminimum resolution of 1 m.. Special Values: <code>Invalid</code>, <code>NoValue</code>, or <code>Unknown: -1000 m</code>.
--     * Slot: provider Description: The provider of the geographical location data.
--     * Slot: region Description: The alphanumeric code that identifies the principal subdivision (e.g. provinceor state) of the country. For example, 'CH-VD' for the Canton of Vaud,Switzerland
-- # Class: User Description: The User object describes the characteristics of a user/person or a securityprincipal.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: credential_uid Description: The unique identifier of the user's credential. For example, AWS Access Key ID.
--     * Slot: display_name Description: The display name of the user, as reported by the product.
--     * Slot: domain Description: The domain where the user is defined. For example: the LDAP or Active Directorydomain.
--     * Slot: email_addr Description: The user's primary email address.
--     * Slot: forward_addr Description: The user's forwarding email address.
--     * Slot: full_name Description: The full name of the user, as reported by the product.
--     * Slot: has_mfa Description: The user has a multi-factor or secondary-factor device assigned.
--     * Slot: name Description: The username. For example, <code>janedoe1</code>.
--     * Slot: phone_number Description: The telephone number of the user.
--     * Slot: risk_level Description: The risk level, normalized to the caption of the risk_level_id value.
--     * Slot: risk_level_id Description: The normalized risk level id.
--     * Slot: risk_score Description: The risk score as reported by the event source.
--     * Slot: type Description: The type of the user. For example, System, AWS IAM User, etc.
--     * Slot: type_id Description: The account type identifier.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The unique user identifier. For example, the Windows user SID, ActiveDirectoryDN or AWS user ARN.
--     * Slot: uid_alt Description: The alternate user identifier. For example, the Active Directory user GUID orAWS user Principal ID.
--     * Slot: account_id Description: The user's account or the account associated with the user.
--     * Slot: ldap_person_id Description: The additional LDAP attributes that describe a person.
--     * Slot: org_id Description: Organization and org unit related to the user.
-- # Class: WebResource Description: The Web Resource object describes characteristics of a web resource that wasaffected by the activity/event.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: data Description: Details of the web resource, e.g, <code>file</code> details,<code>search</code> results or application-defined resource.
--     * Slot: desc Description: Description of the web resource.
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the web resource.
--     * Slot: type Description: The web resource type as defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The unique identifier of the web resource.
--     * Slot: url_string Description: The URL pointing towards the source of the web resource.
--     * Slot: created_time Description: The time when the resource was created.
--     * Slot: modified_time Description: The time when the resource was last modified.
--     * Slot: uid_alt Description: The alternative unique identifier of the resource.
--     * Slot: data_classification_id Description: The Data Classification object includes information about data classificationlevels and data category types.
-- # Class: Device Description: The Device object represents an addressable computer system or host, which istypically connected to a computer network and participates in the transmissionor processing of data within the computer network.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: autoscale_uid Description: The unique identifier of the cloud autoscale configuration.
--     * Slot: boot_time Description: The time the system was booted.
--     * Slot: boot_uid Description: A unique identifier of the device that changes after every reboot. For example,the value of <code>/proc/sys/kernel/random/boot_id</code> from Linux's procfs.
--     * Slot: created_time Description: The time when the device was known to have been created.
--     * Slot: desc Description: The description of the device, ordinarily as reported by the operating system.
--     * Slot: domain Description: The network domain where the device resides. For example:<code>work.example.com</code>.
--     * Slot: eid Description: An Embedded Identity Document, is a unique serial number that identifies aneSIM-enabled device.
--     * Slot: first_seen_time Description: The initial discovery time of the device.
--     * Slot: hostname Description: The device hostname.
--     * Slot: hypervisor Description: The name of the hypervisor running on the device. For example,<code>Xen</code>, <code>VMware</code>, <code>Hyper-V</code>,<code>VirtualBox</code>, etc.
--     * Slot: iccid Description: The Integrated Circuit Card Identification of a mobile device. Typically it isa unique 18 to 22 digit number that identifies a SIM card.
--     * Slot: imei Description: The International Mobile Equipment Identity that is associated with the device.
--     * Slot: ip Description: The device IP address, in either IPv4 or IPv6 format.
--     * Slot: is_backed_up Description: Indicates whether the device or resource has a backup enabled, such as anautomated snapshot or a cloud backup. For example, this is indicated by the<code>cloudBackupEnabled</code> value within JAMF Pro mobile devices or theregistration of an AWS ARN with the AWS Backup service.
--     * Slot: is_compliant Description: The event occurred on a compliant device.
--     * Slot: is_managed Description: The event occurred on a managed device.
--     * Slot: is_mobile_account_active Description: Indicates whether the device has an active mobile account. For example, this isindicated by the <code>itunesStoreAccountActive</code> value within JAMF Promobile devices.
--     * Slot: is_personal Description: The event occurred on a personal device.
--     * Slot: is_shared Description: The event occurred on a shared device.
--     * Slot: is_supervised Description: The event occurred on a supervised device. Devices that are supervised aretypically mobile devices managed by a Mobile Device Management solution and arerestricted from specific behaviors such as Apple AirDrop.
--     * Slot: is_trusted Description: The event occurred on a trusted device.
--     * Slot: last_seen_time Description: The most recent discovery time of the device.
--     * Slot: meid Description: The Mobile Equipment Identifier. It's a unique number that identifies a CodeDivision Multiple Access (CDMA) mobile device.
--     * Slot: model Description: The model of the device. For example <code>ThinkPad X1 Carbon</code>.
--     * Slot: modified_time Description: The time when the device was last known to have been modified.
--     * Slot: name Description: The alternate device name, ordinarily as assigned by an administrator.<p><b>Note:</b> The <b>Name</b> could be any other string that helps toidentify the device, such as a phone number; for example<code>310-555-1234</code>.</p>
--     * Slot: os_machine_uuid Description: The operating system assigned Machine ID. In Windows, this is the value storedat the registry path:<code>HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Cryptography\MachineGuid</code>. InLinux, this is stored in the file: <code>/etc/machine-id</code>.
--     * Slot: region Description: The region where the virtual machine is located. For example, an AWS Region.
--     * Slot: risk_level Description: The risk level, normalized to the caption of the risk_level_id value.
--     * Slot: risk_level_id Description: The normalized risk level id.
--     * Slot: risk_score Description: The risk score as reported by the event source.
--     * Slot: subnet Description: The subnet mask.
--     * Slot: type Description: The device type. For example: <code>unknown</code>, <code>server</code>,<code>desktop</code>, <code>laptop</code>, <code>tablet</code>,<code>mobile</code>, <code>virtual</code>, <code>browser</code>, or<code>other</code>.
--     * Slot: type_id Description: The device type ID.
--     * Slot: udid Description: The Apple assigned Unique Device Identifier (UDID). For iOS, iPadOS, tvOS,watchOS and visionOS devices, this is the UDID. For macOS devices, it is theProvisioning UDID. For example: <code>00008020-008D4548007B4F26</code>
--     * Slot: uid Description: The unique identifier of the device. For example the Windows TargetSID or AWSEC2 ARN.
--     * Slot: uid_alt Description: An alternate unique identifier of the device if any. For example theActiveDirectory DN.
--     * Slot: vendor_name Description: The vendor for the device. For example <code>Dell</code> or<code>Lenovo</code>.
--     * Slot: instance_uid Description: The unique identifier of a VM instance.
--     * Slot: interface_name Description: The name of the network interface (e.g. eth2).
--     * Slot: interface_uid Description: The unique identifier of the network interface.
--     * Slot: mac Description: The Media Access Control (MAC) address of the endpoint.
--     * Slot: mac_vendor Description: The vendor or manufacturer of the endpoint's network interface controller(NIC), as identified from the MAC address.
--     * Slot: subnet_uid Description: The unique identifier of a virtual subnet.
--     * Slot: vlan_uid Description: The Virtual LAN identifier.
--     * Slot: vpc_uid Description: The unique identifier of the Virtual Private Cloud (VPC).
--     * Slot: zone Description: The network zone or LAN segment.
--     * Slot: namespace_pid Description: If running under a process namespace (such as in a container), the processidentifier within that process namespace.
--     * Slot: image_id Description: The image used as a template to run the virtual machine.
--     * Slot: location_id Description: The geographical location of the device.
--     * Slot: org_id Description: Organization and org unit related to the device.
--     * Slot: hw_info_id Description: The endpoint hardware information.
--     * Slot: os_id Description: The endpoint operating system.
--     * Slot: owner_id Description: The identity of the service or user account that owns the endpoint or was lastlogged into it.
--     * Slot: pool_id Description: The pool of desktops or virtual machines to which the endpoint belongs.
--     * Slot: container_id Description: The information describing an instance of a container. A container is aprepackaged, portable system image that runs isolated on an existing systemusing a container runtime like containerd.
-- # Class: FirewallRule Description: The Firewall Rule object represents a specific rule within a firewall policy orevent. It contains information about a rule's configuration, properties, andassociated actions that define how network traffic is handled by the firewall.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: condition Description: The rule trigger condition for the rule. For example: SQL_INJECTION.
--     * Slot: duration Description: The rule response time duration, usually used for challenge completion time.
--     * Slot: match_location Description: The location of the matched data in the source which resulted in the triggeredfirewall rule. For example: HEADER.
--     * Slot: rate_limit Description: The rate limit for a rate-based rule.
--     * Slot: sensitivity Description: The sensitivity of the firewall rule in the matched event. For example: HIGH.
--     * Slot: category Description: The rule category.
--     * Slot: desc Description: The description of the rule that generated the event.
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the rule that generated the event.
--     * Slot: type Description: The rule type.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The unique identifier of the rule that generated the event.
--     * Slot: version Description: The rule version. For example: <code>1.1</code>.
-- # Class: MalwareScanInfo Description: The malware scan information object describes characteristics, metadata of amalware scanning job.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: end_time Description: The timestamp indicating when the scan job completed execution.
--     * Slot: num_files Description: The total number of files analyzed during the scan.
--     * Slot: num_infected Description: The total number of files identified as infected with malware during the scan.
--     * Slot: num_volumes Description: The total number of storage volumes examined during the malware scan.
--     * Slot: size Description: The total size in bytes of all files that were scanned.
--     * Slot: start_time Description: The timestamp indicating when the scan job began execution.
--     * Slot: unique_malware_count Description: The number of unique malware detected across all infected files.
--     * Slot: name Description: The administrator-supplied or application-generated name of the scan. Forexample: "Home office weekly user database scan", "Scan folders for viruses","Full system virus scan"
--     * Slot: type Description: The type of scan.
--     * Slot: type_id Description: The type id of the scan.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The application-defined unique identifier assigned to an instance of a scan.
-- # Class: Process Description: The Process object describes a running instance of a launched program.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: integrity Description: The process integrity level, normalized to the caption of the integrity_idvalue. In the case of 'Other', it is defined by the event source (Windowsonly).
--     * Slot: integrity_id Description: The normalized identifier of the process integrity level (Windows only).
--     * Slot: ptid Description: The identifier of the process thread associated with the event, as returned bythe operating system.
--     * Slot: sandbox Description: The name of the containment jail (i.e., sandbox). For example, hardened_ps,high_security_ps, oracle_ps, netsvcs_ps, or default_ps.
--     * Slot: terminated_time Description: The time when the process was terminated.
--     * Slot: tid Description: The identifier of the thread associated with the event, as returned by theoperating system.
--     * Slot: working_directory Description: The working directory of a process.
--     * Slot: namespace_pid Description: If running under a process namespace (such as in a container), the processidentifier within that process namespace.
--     * Slot: cmd_line Description: The full command line used to launch an application, service, process, or job.For example: <code>ssh user@10.0.0.10</code>. If the command line isunavailable or missing, the empty string <code>''</code> is to be used.
--     * Slot: cpid Description: A unique process identifier that can be assigned deterministically by multiplesystem data producers.
--     * Slot: created_time Description: The time when the process was created/started.
--     * Slot: name Description: The friendly name of the process, for example: <code>Notepad++</code>.
--     * Slot: path Description: The process file path.
--     * Slot: pid Description: The process identifier, as reported by the operating system. Process ID (PID)is a number used by the operating system to uniquely identify an activeprocess.
--     * Slot: uid Description: A unique identifier for this process assigned by the producer (tool).Facilitates correlation of a process event with other events for that process.
--     * Slot: file_id Description: The process file object.
--     * Slot: parent_process_id Description: The parent process of this process object. It is recommended to only populatethis field for the top-level process object, to prevent deep nesting.Additional ancestry information can be supplied in the <code>ancestry</code>attribute.
--     * Slot: session_id Description: The user session under which this process is running.
--     * Slot: user_id Description: The user under which this process is running.
--     * Slot: xattributes_id Description: An unordered collection of zero or more name/value pairs that represent aprocess extended attribute.
--     * Slot: container_id Description: The information describing an instance of a container. A container is aprepackaged, portable system image that runs isolated on an existing systemusing a container runtime like containerd.
-- # Class: AiOperationProfile Description: AI-specific attributes for model operations, retrieval systems, and agentactivities. e.g. model_name, total_token_counts etc.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: ai_model_id Description: The AI Model object describes the characteristics of an AI/ML model. Examplesinclude language models like GPT-4, embedding models liketext-embedding-ada-002, and computer vision models like CLIP.
--     * Slot: message_context_id Description: Communication context for AI system interactions including protocols, roles,clients, and session information for MCP and other AI communication systems.
-- # Class: CloudProfile Description: The attributes that describe information specific to Cloudservices/applications.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: api_id Description: Describes details about a typical API (Application Programming Interface) call.
--     * Slot: cloud_id Description: Describes details about the Cloud environment where the event or finding wascreated.
-- # Class: ContainerProfile Description: The container context for a process.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: namespace_pid Description: If running under a process namespace (such as in a container), the processidentifier within that process namespace.
--     * Slot: container_id Description: The information describing an instance of a container. A container is aprepackaged, portable system image that runs isolated on an existing systemusing a container runtime like containerd.
-- # Class: DataClassificationProfile Description: The Data Classification profile adds attributes to specific resource objects,allowing users to describe information about classifiers & data classificationresults.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: data_classification_id Description: The Data Classification object includes information about data classificationlevels and data category types.
-- # Class: DatetimeProfile Description: This profile defines date/time attributes as defined in RFC-3339. For example1985-04-12T23:20:50.52Z.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: HostProfile Description: The attributes that identify host/device attributes.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: actor_id Description: The actor object describes details about the user/role/process that was thesource of the activity. Note that this is not the threat actor of a campaignbut may be part of a campaign.
--     * Slot: device_id Description: An addressable device, computer system or host.
-- # Class: IncidentProfile Description: The attributes that add incident handling semantics to a Finding.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: impact Description: The impact , normalized to the caption of the impact_id value. In the case of'Other', it is defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: impact_id Description: The normalized impact of the incident or finding. Per NIST, this is themagnitude of harm that can be expected to result from the consequences ofunauthorized disclosure, modification, destruction, or loss of information orinformation system availability.
--     * Slot: impact_score Description: The impact as an integer value of the finding, valid range 0-100.
--     * Slot: is_suspected_breach Description: A determination based on analytics as to whether a potential breach was found.
--     * Slot: priority Description: The priority, normalized to the caption of the priority_id value. In the caseof 'Other', it is defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: priority_id Description: The normalized priority. Priority identifies the relative importance of theincident or finding. It is a measurement of urgency.
--     * Slot: src_url Description: A Url link used to access the original incident.
--     * Slot: verdict Description: The verdict assigned to an Incident finding.
--     * Slot: verdict_id Description: The normalized verdict of an Incident.
--     * Slot: assignee_id Description: The details of the user assigned to an Incident.
--     * Slot: assignee_group_id Description: The details of the group assigned to an Incident.
--     * Slot: ticket_id Description: The linked ticket in the ticketing system.
-- # Class: LoadBalancerProfile Description: The attributes that describe information specific to load balancers.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: load_balancer_id Description: The Load Balancer object contains information related to the device that isdistributing incoming traffic to specified destinations.
-- # Class: NetworkProxyProfile Description: The attributes that identify network proxy attributes.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: proxy_connection_info_id Description: The connection information from the proxy server to the remote server.
--     * Slot: proxy_endpoint_id Description: The proxy (server) in a network connection.
--     * Slot: proxy_http_request_id Description: The HTTP Request from the proxy server to the remote server.
--     * Slot: proxy_http_response_id Description: The HTTP Response from the remote server to the proxy server.
--     * Slot: proxy_tls_id Description: The TLS protocol negotiated between the proxy server and the remote server.
--     * Slot: proxy_traffic_id Description: The network traffic refers to the amount of data moving across a network, fromproxy to remote server at a given point of time.
-- # Class: OsintProfile Description: The OSINT (Open Source Intelligence) profile contains one or more indicatorsand associated analysis and details, such as registrar (WHOIS) information andcommentary about a hostname, or information about a digital certificate and itsusage within a campaign. This information can be used to further enrich adetection or finding by providing decisioning support to other analysts andengineers within the profile itself.
--     * Slot: id
-- # Class: SecurityControlProfile Description: The attributes including disposition that represent the outcome of a securitycontrol including but not limited to access control, malware or policyviolation, network proxy, intrusion detection, firewall, or data control.  Theprofile is intended to augment activities or findings with an outcome when asecurity control has observed or intervened. If the control detected a securityviolation, and the <code>disposition_id</code> or <code>action_id</code> is analertable outcome or action, the <code>is_alert</code> flag may be set to<code>true</code>.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: action Description: The normalized caption of <code>action_id</code>.
--     * Slot: action_id Description: The action taken by a control or other policy-based system leading to anoutcome or disposition. An unknown action may still correspond to a knowndisposition. Refer to <code>disposition_id</code> for the outcome of theaction.
--     * Slot: confidence Description: The confidence, normalized to the caption of the confidence_id value. In thecase of 'Other', it is defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: confidence_id Description: The normalized confidence refers to the accuracy of the rule that created thefinding. A rule with a low confidence means that the finding scope is wide andmay create finding reports that may not be malicious in nature.
--     * Slot: confidence_score Description: The confidence score as reported by the event source.
--     * Slot: disposition Description: The disposition name, normalized to the caption of the disposition_id value. Inthe case of 'Other', it is defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: disposition_id Description: Describes the outcome or action taken by a security control, such as accesscontrol checks, malware detections or various types of policy violations.
--     * Slot: is_alert Description: Indicates that the event is considered to be an alertable signal. Should be setto <code>true</code> if <code>disposition_id = Alert</code> among otherdispositions, and/or <code>risk_level_id</code> or <code>severity_id</code> ofthe event is elevated. Not all control events will be alertable, for example if<code>disposition_id = Exonerated</code> or <code>disposition_id =Allowed</code>.
--     * Slot: risk_details Description: Describes the risk associated with the finding.
--     * Slot: risk_level Description: The risk level, normalized to the caption of the risk_level_id value.
--     * Slot: risk_level_id Description: The normalized risk level id.
--     * Slot: risk_score Description: The risk score as reported by the event source.
--     * Slot: firewall_rule_id Description: The firewall rule that pertains to the control that triggered the event, ifapplicable.
--     * Slot: malware_scan_info_id Description: Describes details about the scan job that identified malware on the targetsystem.
--     * Slot: policy_id Description: The policy that pertains to the control that triggered the event, ifapplicable. For example the name of an anti-malware policy or an access controlpolicy.
-- # Class: TraceProfile Description: The Trace Profile extends the OCSF framework to capture and standardizeobservability events, specifically targeting trace-level data. This profileenables integration and normalization of distributed tracing information,allowing OCSF events to retain essential trace context such as trace IDs, spanrelationships, and service dependencies.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: trace_id Description: The trace object contains information about distributed traces which arecritical to observability and describe how requests move through a system,capturing each step's timing and status.
-- # Class: BaseEvent Description: The base event is a generic and concrete event. It also defines a set ofattributes available in most event classes. As a generic event that does notbelong to any event category, it could be used to log events that are nototherwise defined by the schema.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: activity_id Description: The normalized identifier of the activity that triggered the event.
--     * Slot: activity_name Description: The event activity name, as defined by the activity_id.
--     * Slot: category_name Description: The event category name, as defined by category_uid value.
--     * Slot: category_uid Description: The category unique identifier of the event.
--     * Slot: class_name Description: The event class name, as defined by class_uid value.
--     * Slot: class_uid Description: The unique identifier of a class. A class describes the attributes available inan event.
--     * Slot: count Description: The number of times that events in the same logical group occurred during theevent <strong>Start Time</strong> to <strong>End Time</strong> period.
--     * Slot: duration Description: The event duration or aggregate time, the amount of time the event covers from<code>start_time</code> to <code>end_time</code> in milliseconds.
--     * Slot: end_time Description: The end time of a time period, or the time of the most recent event included inthe aggregate event.
--     * Slot: message Description: The description of the event/finding, as defined by the source.
--     * Slot: raw_data Description: The raw event/finding data as received from the source.
--     * Slot: raw_data_size Description: The size of the raw data which was transformed into an OCSF event, in bytes.
--     * Slot: severity Description: The event/finding severity, normalized to the caption of the<code>severity_id</code> value. In the case of 'Other', it is defined by thesource.
--     * Slot: severity_id Description: <p>The normalized identifier of the event/finding severity.</p>The normalizedseverity is a measurement the effort and expense required to manage and resolvean event or incident. Smaller numerical values represent lower impact events,and larger numerical values represent higher impact events.
--     * Slot: start_time Description: The start time of a time period, or the time of the least recent event includedin the aggregate event.
--     * Slot: status Description: The event status, normalized to the caption of the status_id value. In the caseof 'Other', it is defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: status_code Description: The event status code, as reported by the event source.<br /><br />For example,in a Windows Failed Authentication event, this would be the value of 'FailureCode', e.g. 0x18.
--     * Slot: status_detail Description: The status detail contains additional information about the event/findingoutcome.
--     * Slot: status_id Description: The normalized identifier of the event status.
--     * Slot: time Description: The normalized event occurrence time or the finding creation time.
--     * Slot: timezone_offset Description: The number of minutes that the reported event <code>time</code> is ahead orbehind UTC, in the range -1,080 to +1,080.
--     * Slot: type_name Description: The event/finding type name, as defined by the type_uid.
--     * Slot: type_uid Description: The event/finding type ID. It identifies the event's semantics and structure.The value is calculated by the logging system as: <code>class_uid * 100 +activity_id</code>.
--     * Slot: action Description: The normalized caption of <code>action_id</code>.
--     * Slot: action_id Description: The action taken by a control or other policy-based system leading to anoutcome or disposition. An unknown action may still correspond to a knowndisposition. Refer to <code>disposition_id</code> for the outcome of theaction.
--     * Slot: confidence Description: The confidence, normalized to the caption of the confidence_id value. In thecase of 'Other', it is defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: confidence_id Description: The normalized confidence refers to the accuracy of the rule that created thefinding. A rule with a low confidence means that the finding scope is wide andmay create finding reports that may not be malicious in nature.
--     * Slot: confidence_score Description: The confidence score as reported by the event source.
--     * Slot: disposition Description: The disposition name, normalized to the caption of the disposition_id value. Inthe case of 'Other', it is defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: disposition_id Description: Describes the outcome or action taken by a security control, such as accesscontrol checks, malware detections or various types of policy violations.
--     * Slot: is_alert Description: Indicates that the event is considered to be an alertable signal. Should be setto <code>true</code> if <code>disposition_id = Alert</code> among otherdispositions, and/or <code>risk_level_id</code> or <code>severity_id</code> ofthe event is elevated. Not all control events will be alertable, for example if<code>disposition_id = Exonerated</code> or <code>disposition_id =Allowed</code>.
--     * Slot: risk_details Description: Describes the risk associated with the finding.
--     * Slot: risk_level Description: The risk level, normalized to the caption of the risk_level_id value.
--     * Slot: risk_level_id Description: The normalized risk level id.
--     * Slot: risk_score Description: The risk score as reported by the event source.
--     * Slot: metadata_id Description: The metadata associated with the event or a finding.
--     * Slot: raw_data_hash_id Description: The hash, which describes the content of the raw_data field.
--     * Slot: unmapped_id Description: The attributes that are not mapped to the event schema. The names and values ofthose attributes are specific to the event source.
--     * Slot: api_id Description: Describes details about a typical API (Application Programming Interface) call.
--     * Slot: cloud_id Description: Describes details about the Cloud environment where the event or finding wascreated.
--     * Slot: actor_id Description: The actor object describes details about the user/role/process that was thesource of the activity. Note that this is not the threat actor of a campaignbut may be part of a campaign.
--     * Slot: device_id Description: An addressable device, computer system or host.
--     * Slot: firewall_rule_id Description: The firewall rule that pertains to the control that triggered the event, ifapplicable.
--     * Slot: malware_scan_info_id Description: Describes details about the scan job that identified malware on the targetsystem.
--     * Slot: policy_id Description: The policy that pertains to the control that triggered the event, ifapplicable. For example the name of an anti-malware policy or an access controlpolicy.
