--     * Slot: confidence Description: The confidence, normalized to the caption of the confidence_id value. In thecase of 'Other', it is defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: confidence_id Description: The normalized confidence refers to the accuracy of the rule that created thefinding. A rule with a low confidence means that the finding scope is wide andmay create finding reports that may not be malicious in nature.
--     * Slot: confidence_score Description: The confidence score as reported by the event source.
--     * Slot: disposition Description: The disposition name, normalized to the caption of the disposition_id value. Inthe case of 'Other', it is defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: disposition_id Description: Describes the outcome or action taken by a security control, such as accesscontrol checks, malware detections or various types of policy violations.
--     * Slot: is_alert Description: Indicates that the event is considered to be an alertable signal. Should be setto <code>true</code> if <code>disposition_id = Alert</code> among otherdispositions, and/or <code>risk_level_id</code> or <code>severity_id</code> ofthe event is elevated. Not all control events will be alertable, for example if<code>disposition_id = Exonerated</code> or <code>disposition_id =Allowed</code>.
--     * Slot: risk_details Description: Describes the risk associated with the finding.
--     * Slot: risk_level Description: The risk level, normalized to the caption of the risk_level_id value.
--     * Slot: risk_level_id Description: The normalized risk level id.
--     * Slot: risk_score Description: The risk score as reported by the event source.
--     * Slot: connection_info_id Description: The network connection information.
--     * Slot: cumulative_traffic_id Description: The cumulative (running total) network traffic aggregated from the start of aflow or session. Use when reporting: (1) total accumulated bytes/packets sinceflow initiation, (2) combined aggregation models where both incremental deltasand running totals are reported together (populate both <code>traffic</code>for the delta and this attribute for the cumulative total), or (3) finalsummary metrics when a long-lived connection closes. This represents the sum ofall activity from flow start to the current observation, not a delta orpoint-in-time value.
--     * Slot: dst_endpoint_id Description: The responder (server) in a network connection.
--     * Slot: network_observation_point_id Description: The network endpoint that observes or inspects network traffic as a third-partysystem, used when the observer is neither the source nor the destination of thecommunication (when <code>observation_point_id</code> = 3). Examples includenetwork taps, span ports, inline security devices, or packet capture systemsthat monitor traffic between other endpoints.
--     * Slot: proxy_id Description: The proxy (server) in a network connection.
--     * Slot: src_endpoint_id Description: The initiator (client) of the network connection.
--     * Slot: tls_id Description: The Transport Layer Security (TLS) attributes.
--     * Slot: traffic_id Description: The network traffic for this observation period. Use when reporting: (1) deltavalues (bytes/packets transferred since the last observation), (2)instantaneous measurements at a specific point in time, or (3) standalonesingle-event metrics. This attribute represents a point-in-time measurement orincremental change, not a running total. For accumulated totals across multipleobservations or the lifetime of a flow, use <code>cumulative_traffic</code>instead.
--     * Slot: proxy_connection_info_id Description: The connection information from the proxy server to the remote server.
--     * Slot: proxy_endpoint_id Description: The proxy (server) in a network connection.
--     * Slot: proxy_http_request_id Description: The HTTP Request from the proxy server to the remote server.
--     * Slot: proxy_http_response_id Description: The HTTP Response from the remote server to the proxy server.
--     * Slot: proxy_tls_id Description: The TLS protocol negotiated between the proxy server and the remote server.
--     * Slot: proxy_traffic_id Description: The network traffic refers to the amount of data moving across a network, fromproxy to remote server at a given point of time.
--     * Slot: load_balancer_id Description: The Load Balancer object contains information related to the device that isdistributing incoming traffic to specified destinations.
--     * Slot: metadata_id Description: The metadata associated with the event or a finding.
--     * Slot: raw_data_hash_id Description: The hash, which describes the content of the raw_data field.
--     * Slot: unmapped_id Description: The attributes that are not mapped to the event schema. The names and values ofthose attributes are specific to the event source.
--     * Slot: api_id Description: Describes details about a typical API (Application Programming Interface) call.
--     * Slot: cloud_id Description: Describes details about the Cloud environment where the event or finding wascreated.
--     * Slot: actor_id Description: The actor object describes details about the user/role/process that was thesource of the activity. Note that this is not the threat actor of a campaignbut may be part of a campaign.
--     * Slot: device_id Description: An addressable device, computer system or host.
--     * Slot: firewall_rule_id Description: The firewall rule that pertains to the control that triggered the event, ifapplicable.
--     * Slot: malware_scan_info_id Description: Describes details about the scan job that identified malware on the targetsystem.
--     * Slot: policy_id Description: The policy that pertains to the control that triggered the event, ifapplicable. For example the name of an anti-malware policy or an access controlpolicy.
-- # Class: RdpActivity Description: Remote Desktop Protocol (RDP) Activity events report post-authentication remoteclient connections between clients and servers over the network.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: activity_id Description: The normalized identifier of the activity that triggered the event.
--     * Slot: identifier_cookie Description: The client identifier cookie during client/server exchange.
