-- # Class: WindowsQueryEvidence Description: The resulting evidence information that was queried.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: query_type Description: The normalized caption of query_type_id or the source-specific query type.
--     * Slot: query_type_id Description: The normalized type of system query performed against a device or systemcomponent.
--     * Slot: state Description: The state of the socket, normalized to the caption of the state_id value. Inthe case of 'Other', it is defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: tcp_state_id Description: The state of the TCP socket for the network connection.
--     * Slot: reg_key_id Description: The registry key object describes a Windows registry key.
--     * Slot: reg_value_id Description: The registry key object describes a Windows registry value.
--     * Slot: connection_info_id Description: The network connection information related to a Network Connection query type.
--     * Slot: file_id Description: The file that is the target of the query when query_type_id indicates a Filequery.
--     * Slot: folder_id Description: The folder that is the target of the query when query_type_id indicates aFolder query.
--     * Slot: group_id Description: The administrative group that is the target of the query when query_type_idindicates an Admin Group query.
--     * Slot: job_id Description: The job object that pertains to the event when query_type_id indicates a Jobquery.
--     * Slot: kernel_id Description: The kernel object that pertains to the event when query_type_id indicates aKernel query.
--     * Slot: module_id Description: The module that pertains to the event when query_type_id indicates a Modulequery.
--     * Slot: peripheral_device_id Description: The peripheral device that triggered the event when query_type_id indicates aPeripheral Device query.
--     * Slot: process_id Description: The process that pertains to the event when query_type_id indicates a Processquery.
--     * Slot: service_id Description: The service that pertains to the event when query_type_id indicates a Servicequery.
--     * Slot: session_id Description: The authenticated user or service session when query_type_id indicates aSession query.
--     * Slot: startup_item_id Description: The startup item object that pertains to the event when query_type_id indicatesa Startup Item query.
--     * Slot: user_id Description: The user that pertains to the event when query_type_id indicates a User query.
-- # Class: RegKey Description: The registry key object describes a Windows registry key.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: is_system Description: The indication of whether the object is part of the operating system.
--     * Slot: modified_time Description: The time when the registry key was last modified.
--     * Slot: path Description: The full path to the registry key.
--     * Slot: security_descriptor Description: The security descriptor of the registry key.
-- # Class: RegValue Description: The registry value object describes a Windows registry value.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: data Description: The data of the registry value. Where the value type is known, implementersshould instead use a type-specific attribute, i.e.<code>reg_binary_data</code>, <code>reg_integer_data</code>,<code>reg_string_data</code>, or <code>reg_string_list_data</code>.
--     * Slot: is_default Description: The indication of whether the value is from a default value name. For example,the value name could be missing.
--     * Slot: is_system Description: The indication of whether the object is part of the operating system.
--     * Slot: modified_time Description: The time when the registry value was last modified.
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the registry value.
--     * Slot: path Description: The full path to the registry key, where the value is located.
--     * Slot: reg_binary_data Description: The data of the registry value when <code>type_id</code> is<code>REG_BINARY</code> or <code>REG_NONE</code>.
--     * Slot: reg_integer_data Description: The data of the registry value when <code>type_id</code> is<code>REG_DWORD</code>, <code>REG_DWORD_BIG_ENDIAN</code>, or<code>REG_QWORD</code>.
--     * Slot: reg_string_data Description: The data of the registry value when <code>type_id</code> is<code>REG_SZ</code>, <code>REG_EXPAND_SZ</code>, or <code>REG_LINK</code>.
--     * Slot: type Description: A string representation of the value type as specified in <a target='_blank'href='https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/sysinfo/registry-value-types'>RegistryValue Types</a>.
--     * Slot: type_id Description: The value type ID.
-- # Class: WindowsStartupItem Description: The startup item object describes an application component that has associatedstartup criteria and configurations.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: name Description: The unique name of the startup item.
--     * Slot: run_state Description: The run state of the startup item.
--     * Slot: run_state_id Description: The run state ID of the startup item.
--     * Slot: start_type Description: The start type of the startup item.
--     * Slot: start_type_id Description: The start type ID of the startup item.
--     * Slot: type Description: The startup item type.
--     * Slot: type_id Description: The startup item type identifier.
--     * Slot: win_service_id Description: The startup item Windows service resource.
--     * Slot: driver_id Description: The startup item kernel driver resource.
--     * Slot: job_id Description: The startup item job resource.
--     * Slot: process_id Description: The startup item process resource.
-- # Class: WinResource Description: The Windows resource object describes a resource object managed by Windows,such as mutant or timer.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: details Description: The string detailing the attributes of the resource object.
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the resource object.
--     * Slot: svc_name Description: The Windows service acting as the object server for the resource object, suchas Security or Security Account Manager.
--     * Slot: type Description: The type of the Windows resource object.
--     * Slot: type_id Description: The normalized type identifier of the Windows resource object accessed.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The Windows provided handle identifier for the resource object
--     * Slot: created_time Description: The time when the resource was created.
--     * Slot: data Description: Additional data describing the resource.
--     * Slot: modified_time Description: The time when the resource was last modified.
--     * Slot: uid_alt Description: The alternative unique identifier of the resource.
--     * Slot: data_classification_id Description: The Data Classification object includes information about data classificationlevels and data category types.
-- # Class: WinService Description: The Windows Service object describes a Windows service.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: cmd_line Description: The full command line used to launch the service.
--     * Slot: load_order_group Description: The name of the load ordering group of which this service is a member.
--     * Slot: name Description: The unique name of the service.
--     * Slot: service_category Description: The service category, normalized to the caption of the service_category_idvalue. In the case of 'Other', it is defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: service_category_id Description: The normalized identifier of the service category.
--     * Slot: service_error_control Description: The service error control, normalized to the caption of the<code>service_error_control_id</code> value. In the case of 'Other', it isdefined by the event source.
--     * Slot: service_error_control_id Description: The normalized identifier of the service error control.
--     * Slot: service_start_name Description: For a user mode service, this attribute represents the name of the accountunder which the service is run. For a kernel mode driver, this attributerepresents the object name used to load the driver.
--     * Slot: service_start_type Description: The service start type, normalized to the caption of the<code>service_start_type_id</code> value. In the case of 'Other', it is definedby the event source.
--     * Slot: service_start_type_id Description: The normalized identifier of the service start type.
--     * Slot: service_type Description: The service type, normalized to the caption of the service_type_id value. Inthe case of 'Other', it is defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: service_type_id Description: The normalized identifier of the service type.
--     * Slot: uid Description: The unique identifier of the service.
--     * Slot: version Description: The version of the service.
--     * Slot: hosting_process_id Description: The process that is hosting this service.
--     * Slot: service_dll_file_id Description: For a shared user mode service (<code>service_type_id</code> is 4) this is theDLL that gets loaded by the generic service host process (e.g.<code>svchost.exe</code>) to implement the service.
--     * Slot: service_file_id Description: For a user mode service (<code>service_type_id</code> 3 or 4) this is theexecutable program that the SCM launches as the service process.<br>For akernel mode driver (<code>service_type_id</code> 1 or 2) this is the driverfile loaded into the kernel at the request of the SCM.
-- # Class: PrefetchQuery Description: Prefetch Query events report information about Windows prefetch files.
--     * Slot: id
--     * Slot: last_run_time Description: The prefetch file last run time.
--     * Slot: name Description: The name of the prefetch file that is the target of the query.
--     * Slot: run_count Description: The prefetch file run count.
--     * Slot: activity_id Description: The normalized identifier of the activity that triggered the event.
--     * Slot: query_result Description: The result of the query.
--     * Slot: query_result_id Description: The normalized identifier of the query result.
--     * Slot: activity_name Description: The event activity name, as defined by the activity_id.
--     * Slot: category_name Description: The event category name, as defined by category_uid value.
--     * Slot: category_uid Description: The category unique identifier of the event.
--     * Slot: class_name Description: The event class name, as defined by class_uid value.
--     * Slot: class_uid Description: The unique identifier of a class. A class describes the attributes available inan event.
--     * Slot: count Description: The number of times that events in the same logical group occurred during theevent <strong>Start Time</strong> to <strong>End Time</strong> period.
--     * Slot: duration Description: The event duration or aggregate time, the amount of time the event covers from<code>start_time</code> to <code>end_time</code> in milliseconds.
--     * Slot: end_time Description: The end time of a time period, or the time of the most recent event included inthe aggregate event.
--     * Slot: message Description: The description of the event/finding, as defined by the source.
--     * Slot: raw_data Description: The raw event/finding data as received from the source.
--     * Slot: raw_data_size Description: The size of the raw data which was transformed into an OCSF event, in bytes.
--     * Slot: severity Description: The event/finding severity, normalized to the caption of the<code>severity_id</code> value. In the case of 'Other', it is defined by thesource.
--     * Slot: severity_id Description: <p>The normalized identifier of the event/finding severity.</p>The normalizedseverity is a measurement the effort and expense required to manage and resolvean event or incident. Smaller numerical values represent lower impact events,and larger numerical values represent higher impact events.
--     * Slot: start_time Description: The start time of a time period, or the time of the least recent event includedin the aggregate event.
--     * Slot: status Description: The event status, normalized to the caption of the status_id value. In the caseof 'Other', it is defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: status_code Description: The event status code, as reported by the event source.<br /><br />For example,in a Windows Failed Authentication event, this would be the value of 'FailureCode', e.g. 0x18.
--     * Slot: status_detail Description: The status detail contains additional information about the event/findingoutcome.
--     * Slot: status_id Description: The normalized identifier of the event status.
--     * Slot: time Description: The normalized event occurrence time or the finding creation time.
--     * Slot: timezone_offset Description: The number of minutes that the reported event <code>time</code> is ahead orbehind UTC, in the range -1,080 to +1,080.
--     * Slot: type_name Description: The event/finding type name, as defined by the type_uid.
--     * Slot: type_uid Description: The event/finding type ID. It identifies the event's semantics and structure.The value is calculated by the logging system as: <code>class_uid * 100 +activity_id</code>.
--     * Slot: action Description: The normalized caption of <code>action_id</code>.
--     * Slot: action_id Description: The action taken by a control or other policy-based system leading to anoutcome or disposition. An unknown action may still correspond to a knowndisposition. Refer to <code>disposition_id</code> for the outcome of theaction.
--     * Slot: confidence Description: The confidence, normalized to the caption of the confidence_id value. In thecase of 'Other', it is defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: confidence_id Description: The normalized confidence refers to the accuracy of the rule that created thefinding. A rule with a low confidence means that the finding scope is wide andmay create finding reports that may not be malicious in nature.
--     * Slot: confidence_score Description: The confidence score as reported by the event source.
--     * Slot: disposition Description: The disposition name, normalized to the caption of the disposition_id value. Inthe case of 'Other', it is defined by the event source.
--     * Slot: disposition_id Description: Describes the outcome or action taken by a security control, such as accesscontrol checks, malware detections or various types of policy violations.
--     * Slot: is_alert Description: Indicates that the event is considered to be an alertable signal. Should be setto <code>true</code> if <code>disposition_id = Alert</code> among otherdispositions, and/or <code>risk_level_id</code> or <code>severity_id</code> ofthe event is elevated. Not all control events will be alertable, for example if<code>disposition_id = Exonerated</code> or <code>disposition_id =Allowed</code>.
--     * Slot: risk_details Description: Describes the risk associated with the finding.
--     * Slot: risk_level Description: The risk level, normalized to the caption of the risk_level_id value.
--     * Slot: risk_level_id Description: The normalized risk level id.
--     * Slot: risk_score Description: The risk score as reported by the event source.
--     * Slot: query_info_id Description: The search details associated with the query request.
--     * Slot: metadata_id Description: The metadata associated with the event or a finding.
--     * Slot: raw_data_hash_id Description: The hash, which describes the content of the raw_data field.
--     * Slot: unmapped_id Description: The attributes that are not mapped to the event schema. The names and values ofthose attributes are specific to the event source.
--     * Slot: api_id Description: Describes details about a typical API (Application Programming Interface) call.
--     * Slot: cloud_id Description: Describes details about the Cloud environment where the event or finding wascreated.
--     * Slot: actor_id Description: The actor object describes details about the user/role/process that was thesource of the activity. Note that this is not the threat actor of a campaignbut may be part of a campaign.
--     * Slot: device_id Description: An addressable device, computer system or host.
--     * Slot: firewall_rule_id Description: The firewall rule that pertains to the control that triggered the event, ifapplicable.
--     * Slot: malware_scan_info_id Description: Describes details about the scan job that identified malware on the targetsystem.
--     * Slot: policy_id Description: The policy that pertains to the control that triggered the event, ifapplicable. For example the name of an anti-malware policy or an access controlpolicy.
